s0">sults because fallen natures are predisposed to choose sin. We were born </div><div class="t m15c x98 h29 y5b9 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with a natural bent toward evil. Prior to the new birth experience (justifica-</div><div class="t m460 x98 h29 y625 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tion) sin was natural to us all. </div><div class="t m461 x3 h29 y5bb ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The important point is that for all humanity condemnation to eternal </div><div class="t m2fd x98 h29 y5bc ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">death was abolished by Christ&apos;s sacrifice. (See John 6:33; Rom. 8:1.) </div><div class="t m462 x98 h29 y5bd ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Such condemnation is earned again by those who reject Christ and choose </div><div class="t m16f x98 h29 y5be ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sin. (See John 3:18, 36.) </div><div class="t m463 x98 h24 y626 ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ARE YOU ENJOYING LIFE IN CHRIST? </div><div class="t m464 x72 h29 y626 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Do you have the inner as-</div><div class="t m24c x98 h29 y627 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">surance of freedom from condemnation? How do you plan to share this ex-</div><div class="t m31a x98 h29 y628 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">perience with others? What major points in Romans chapter 5 would you </div><div class="t m27b x98 h29 y629 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fmd helpful in witnessing to those about you? </div><div class="t m465 xc6 h4e y62a ff3 fs26 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">n</div><div class="t m30d x84 h24 y5c ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">FURTHER STUDY AND MEDITATION: </div><div class="t m466 x68 h29 y5c ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Read the last portion of </div><div class="t m137 x84 h29 y62b ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;The Temptation and Fall&quot; in </div><div class="t m3e6 x56 h29 y62c ff7 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Patriarchs and Prophets, </div><div class="t m3d5 x91 h29 y62c ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pp. 59-62. </div><div class="t m41e x84 h24 y62d ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SUMMARY: </div><div class="t m467 x9 h29 y62d ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 